    "path": "src/common/config",
    "name": "config",
    "purpose": "Strongly typed TOML configuration model and fallible loader. config.rs owns config-file discovery, credential resolution, runtime path normalization including client and server Marix paths, default CoreConfig fallback when TOML omits core, symmetric client/host connection settings via ClientConfig and HostConfig, and server endpoint settings via ServerConfig; sys.rs owns supported OS/architecture detection through serializable System, Platform, and Arch types with System::new and the private Ubuntu detector; mod.rs re-exports the public config surface including ServerConfig, TelemetryConfig, ToolConfig, and system types.",
